Class FudgeFieldType<TValue>

public class FudgeFieldType<TValue>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

The class defining the type of a particular field. While Fudge comes with a set of required types which are fully supported in all Fudge-compliant systems, if you have custom data, you can control the encoding using your own instance of FudgeFieldType, making sure to register the instance with the FudgeTypeDictionary at application startup.
